'''Delabar State Park''' is an [[List of Illinois state parks|Illinois state park]] on {{convert|89|acre}} in [[Henderson County, Illinois|Henderson County]], [[Illinois]], [[United States]]. Two brothers, [[Roy Delabar|Roy]] and [[Jack Delabar]] donated the site of the park in 1959. The park was named after the two brothers, and officially opened in 1960.

