This is a '''list of forests in Denmark'''.
==Overview== In the year 2000, Denmark had 4860&nbsp;km², corresponding to 11% of the Danish territory. Of this, 69% was located in [[Jutland]] while 31% was located on the islands. 63% was [[Temperate coniferous forest|coniferous forest]] while 37% was [[Temperate broadleaf and mixed forests|broadleaf forest]].<ref name=Skovital>{{cite web|url=http://www.trae.dk/index.asp?page=/dokumenter/dokument.asp%3FDokumentID%3D1092|title=Danmarks skove i tal|publisher=Dansk Skovforening|accessdate=2010-01-04|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120308120621/http://www.trae.dk/index.asp?page=%2Fdokumenter%2Fdokument.asp%3FDokumentID%3D1092|archivedate=2012-03-08|df=}}</ref>
